data.title: Stacey Dash's ex Jeffrey Marty 'claims hypnotic prayer techniques were used and wants annulment'
data.meta_description: The lawyer is said to have claimed he only got married to the Clueless star, 53, in April 2018 - just 10 days after they first met - when 'hypnotic prayer techniques' were used by a pastor.
data.text:
Stacey Dash's estranged husband Jeffrey Marty has asked a judge to annul their marriage after claiming he was 'hypnotised' into the union.

The lawyer is said to have claimed he only got married to the Clueless star, 53, in April 2018 - just 10 days after they first met - when 'hypnotic prayer techniques' were used by a pastor who put 'serious religious pressure on him'.

The actress announced in April that the couple had ended their marriage and in June she filed for a divorce petition in Pasco County, Florida.

According to legal documents obtained by TMZ on Wednesday, Jeffrey has now filed new court papers in response to her divorce petition.

The website claims the lawyer only married Stacey as 10 days before their wedding her pastor 'unexpectedly and suddenly proclaimed that it was God's will' that they got married.

Jeffrey has also reportedly cited that he was unable to consent to the nuptials as 'hypnotic prayer techniques' were used and there was 'pressure from other clergies'.

TMZ claims that the lawyer hasn't described the 'hypnotic' techniques used while Stacey's attorneys 'don't fully admit' to the claims.

The actress' legal team have reportedly said that he 'didn't show any unusual signs about his mental state at the time' and have also asked for an annulment.

Stacey Dash's representatives told MailOnline: 'In our country, people are free to say whatever they want regardless if their statement is baseless. That’s what makes America so great.'

'With that being said, Stacey also filed her response in saying that she was unaware of her estranged husband mental state at the time of her marriage. With the line made famous by the film War Games “Sometimes the only way to win is not to play.” Stacey hopes her case will be finalized soon.'

Stacey filed for divorce from her fourth husband Jeffrey in June after nearly two years.

The 53-year-old actress filed her divorce petition in Pasco County, Florida according to legal documents obtained by TMZ at the time.

She is said to have listed the date of separation on October 1, 2019 which was just a year-and-a-half after they married on April 6, 2018.

The documents also revealed that the two had not owned any personal property jointly which would need to be divided.

Stacey also claimed her income to be $2,500 per month.

Back on April 30, the actress addressed her 157K followers on Instagram as she made the announcement that she was moving on from her fourth husband.

'My husband and I have made the hard decision of ending our marriage. After much prayer, I feel this is the right path for both of us,' she wrote.

She added: 'I wish him nothing but the best. Thank you everyone for your support and respecting our privacy during this difficult time'.

The Clueless star and lawyer married in April 2018 in Florida reportedly just 10 days after they first met.

Stacey was arrested for investigation of domestic battery in September in Florida.

Body camera footage of her arrest showed Dash handcuffed while being placed in the back of a squad car.

Dash had called police to her Florida home claiming that her husband had placed her in a chokehold.

She was arrested for investigation of domestic battery after Pasco County Sheriff's Office deputies who arrived on the scene observed that Jeffrey had red scratch marks on his left arm.

Stacey was bailed out of jail by her husband and prosecutors in Florida dropped their domestic battery case against her in October.

The New York City native rose to fame portraying Dionne Davenport in the 1995 film Clueless starring Alicia Silverstone, 43.

Dash was previously married to Brian Lovell, James Maby and Emmanuel Xuereb.

She has a 16-year-old daughter Lola with Lovell and 28-year-old son Austin Williams from a previous relationship with singer Christopher Williams, 52.

Dash also played Dionne in the TV series Clueless from 1996 to 1999.

She was a contributor on Fox News from 2014 to 2016.
